narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is what you make of it. I would absolutely take it again. It definitely applies to those outside the theater studies department -- the material is really important for anyone who has a body!
I would certainly recommend it. Body training is important, especially for theater artists, and thinking about what the body is and how it exists day-to-day is a valuable train of thought.

I can't speak for theater studies majors, but this was my most unconventional class this semester, and a bright spot in my Tuesday afternoons between two seminars in Econ and Global Affairs. Intellectually, I wasn't very stretched though.
